ref: Add comparison operation test files
Introduced new PHP files for various comparison operations. These files cover inequality, greater-than, and less-than-or-equal comparisons among different data types including integers, strings, booleans, arrays, and null values. This enhances test coverage and thoroughness of comparison scenarios in the project.

task.summary:
fix: Remove obsolete test files and refactor remaining tests
Deleted several obsolete test files from the repository as they were no longer relevant. Refactored remaining tests to streamline the naming conventions and improve readability. This ensures all test files are up-to-date and follow a consistent structure.

fix: Refactor and reorganize PHP codebase
Deleted an unnecessary file and introduced new files for phase tasks. Refactored existing classes and functions, renaming and reorganizing them into appropriate directories. Improved code readability and consistency in method names and function structures.

chore: Remove redundant PHP test files
Removed multiple PHP test files related to arithmetic, bitwise, logical, casting, and null coalescing operations. These files were redundant and not currently in use, helping to clean up the repository and reduce clutter.

ref: Add comparison operation test files

These files cover inequality, greater-than, and less-than-or-equal comparisons among different data types including integers, strings, booleans, arrays, and null values. This enhances test coverage and thoroughness of comparison scenarios in the project.
